div.p: As per the task data is stored in Clickhouse DB. After some initial research these are my findings about Clickhouse DB:

ol.li: Primary Key is not unique per row but a grouping granule to batch index records
If no primary key is specified, then it will consider sorting keys as primary keys

div.p: I will be using these features to design the pipeline and set of tables.

g.text: currency VARCHAR NOT NULL COMMENT 'Currency Code',
country VARCHAR NOT NULL COMMENT 'Country name',
description String NULL COMMENT 'Any description about currency code',

div.p: Exchange rate table is grouped by currency first and ordered by date

ul.li: this allows for data skipping while making a join with the table

g.text: currency VARCHAR NOT NULL COMMENT 'Currency Code',
date DATE NOT NULL COMMENT 'Date for which exchange rate is recorded',
